@startuml sequence_deactivation
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title User Deactivation with Immediate Token Blacklist

actor "Admin" as Admin
participant "UsersController" as Ctrl
database "FleetHubDbContext" as DB
participant "IUserBlacklist" as BL
participant "TenantContextMiddleware" as TCM

== Admin Deactivates User ==

Admin -> Ctrl: PUT /api/v1/users/{id}/deactivate
Ctrl -> DB: user.IsActive = false
Ctrl -> DB: SaveChangesAsync()
DB --> Ctrl: saved
Ctrl -> BL: Add(userId)
note right of BL: ConcurrentDictionary\nAuto-expires after 30 min\n(JWT max lifetime)
BL --> Ctrl: stored
Ctrl --> Admin: 200 OK { user }

== Deactivated User Attempts Access ==

actor "Deactivated User" as DU
DU -> TCM: GET /api/v1/equipment\nBearer <still-valid-JWT>
TCM -> TCM: Extract EntraObjectId
TCM -> BL: IsBlacklisted(userId)?
BL --> TCM: **true**
TCM --> DU: **403 Forbidden**\n"Account deactivated"

== Admin Reactivates User ==

Admin -> Ctrl: PUT /api/v1/users/{id}/activate
Ctrl -> DB: user.IsActive = true
Ctrl -> DB: SaveChangesAsync()
Ctrl -> BL: Remove(userId)
BL --> Ctrl: removed
Ctrl --> Admin: 200 OK { user }

== Reactivated User Regains Access ==

DU -> TCM: GET /api/v1/equipment
TCM -> BL: IsBlacklisted(userId)?
BL --> TCM: **false**
TCM -> DB: FindUser (IsActive=true)
TCM -> TCM: Proceed with normal resolution
TCM --> DU: Request continues to controller

@enduml
